  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Leaflet</ab>
      <ab subtype="creation" type="lido:event">
        <date>1933 after</date>
      </ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">A framed leaflet produced by the ‘Korzo’ cinema in Jakšić Street 9 announces the screening of ‘Dvorac na jugu’ (the Serbo-Croatian translation of the original German film title ‘Das Schloss im Süden’). The film was billed as ‘the most beautiful operetta of this season’, with Liane Haid and Viktor de Kowa in the leading roles, Géza von Bolváry as director and music by Franz Grothe: ‘This film was shot in Dalmatia and on our Adriatic’.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The film was released in 1933. The ‘Korzo’ cinema was located in Belgrade.</ab>
